HOW DID IT APPERS IN SOC MONITORS?
Protocol : what we see in SIEM                : the expect attack possible.
TCP      : alot of SYN without ACK            : SYN FLOOD (DDoS)          .
TCP      : one connetiion with multiple ports : Port Scanning             .
UDP      : unecpect encreas in the Bandwidth  : UDP Flood / DDoS          .
UDP      : huge/Repeted DNS request           : Amplification / Tunneling .

SOC Note: A flood of SYN packs without ACKs = SYN Flood (DDoS).


